Inventory Management System
1. Abstract
 An Inventory Management System is a software application used to track, manage, and control stock levels, orders, sales, and deliveries. It helps businesses maintain optimal inventory, reduce losses, and improve efficiency. The system stores product details in an organized manner and allows quick access to stock information. It also helps in generating reports for better decision-making and smooth business operations.
2. Introduction
 Inventory management is an essential part of any business that deals with products. Manual tracking can lead to errors, missing records, and inefficiencies. This system automates stock handling, making the process faster and more accurate. It ensures that products are available when needed and avoids overstocking or shortages. With digital management, businesses can improve productivity and customer satisfaction.
3. Objective
